Authors: Utama D.N., Mitchell A., Fieri B., Richard H.
Title: A Simple Butterfly Lifecycle Algorithm for Measuring Company's Growth Performance
Source title: IOP Conference Series: Materials Science and Engineering
Affiliations: Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Computer Science Department, School of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Utama, D.N., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Mitchell, A., Computer Science Department, School of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Fieri, B., Computer Science Department, School of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Richard, H., Computer Science Department, School of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Abstract: Five states of butterfly metamorphoses in its lifecycle naturally inspire algorithm creation. A simple butterfly lifecycle algorithm (BLCA) was successfully created by imitating a real butterfly lifecycle in five stages study; preliminary analysis, literature review, input-process-output analysis, logic analysis, and algorithm construction. The algorithm was represented thru activity diagram, pseudo-code, and class diagram. The dummy case of measuring company growth performance used to experimentally test the algorithm. © Published under licence by IOP Publishing Ltd.
Index Keywords: Risk management; Activity diagram; Class diagrams; Growth performance; Literature reviews; Logic analysis; Preliminary analysis; Process output; Pseudo codes; Systems engineering
